                  "blocks": {
                    "text_F7FC4H": {
                      "type": "text",
                      "settings": {
                        "text": "<p>They’re both New Zealand native honeys, but they’re made from different trees and they taste different. <strong>Mānuka</strong> tends to be darker and more intense, and it’s the one that can be independently graded and certified under the <strong>UMF™</strong> system. <strong>Kānuka</strong> is typically lighter and more floral. We use both for a softer sweetness and more flavour than refined sugar. Learn more: <a href=\"/pages/ingredients\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Ingredients\">Ingredients</a></p>",
                        "width": "100%",
